16
00:01:15,450 --> 00:01:19,780
had to look through every single site to
find the one you wanted, it would just take forever.

17
00:01:19,780 --> 00:01:23,490
So to make your search faster,
search engines are constantly scanning

18
00:01:23,490 --> 00:01:28,400
the web in advance to record the
information that might help with your search later.

19
00:01:28,400 --> 00:01:32,220
That way when you search
about "travel to Mars" the search engine

20
00:01:32,220 --> 00:01:35,280
already has what it needs to give you an
answer in real time.

21
00:01:36,340 --> 00:01:37,880
Here's how it works:

22
00:01:37,880 --> 00:01:42,340
The internet is a web of pages connected
to each other by hyperlinks.

23
00:01:42,340 --> 00:01:46,500
Search engines are constantly running a program
called "spider" that crawls through

24
00:01:46,500 --> 00:01:49,660
these web pages to collect information
about them.

25
00:01:49,660 --> 00:01:57,120
Each time it finds a hyperlink, it follows it until it has
visited every page it can find on the entire internet.

26
00:01:57,120 --> 00:02:00,600
For each page of the
spider visits, it records any information

27
00:02:00,600 --> 00:02:06,680
it might need for a search by adding it to
a special database called a search index.

