41
00:03:11,360 --> 00:03:14,260
The idea is that if lots of websites think that a

42
00:03:14,260 --> 00:03:17,820
web page is interesting, then it's
probably the one you're looking for.

43
00:03:17,820 --> 00:03:23,000
This algorithm was called "Page Rank", not because it ranks web pages, but because

44
00:03:23,000 --> 00:03:27,220
it was named after its inventor, Larry
Page, who is one of the founders of Google.

45
00:03:27,620 --> 00:03:32,020
Because the website often makes money
when you visit it, spammers are constantly

46
00:03:32,020 --> 00:03:37,920
